strings: <se_low>Yangus: Who in 'is right mind would build an 'ouse all the way up 'ere, eh!?
<se_low>Yangus: I'm absolutely knackered after all that climbin'!
<se_high>Jessica: The scenery's gorgeous and the house looks nice from the outside, but it's kind of cramped inside. Don't you think?

<se_high>Jessica: And that's the guy who lives here...
What a let down!
<se_def>Angelo: I thought maybe there'd be a beautiful woman living up here all alone...
<se_def>Angelo: There's no justice in the world!
<se_low>Yangus: If we've gotta bring it back 'ere once we find it, it means we gotta climb all that way again!
<se_low>Yangus: Urgh! Just the thought of it's enough to wear a man out!

<se_high>Jessica: This red tree sounds kind of interesting.
It's worth going just to take a look.

<se_high>Jessica: And while we're there, we may as well get his tool bag for him.
Come on! Let's find the tree!
<se_def>Angelo: I don't really see why we should put ourselves out for that shabby-looking creature.

<se_def>Angelo: Huh! You're all too soft!
Why did I have to end up travelling with a group of pushovers!
<se_low>Yangus: The quicker we 'and over that bag, the quicker we get our reward! An' it's too close-to-phobic to stay 'ere much longer, anyway.
<se_high>Jessica: Oh yeah. He said something about giving us a reward if we took back his tool bag.
<se_high>Jessica: It's a bit of a pain climbing up and down here, but I'd be interested to see what this reward of his is!
<se_def>Angelo: Oh, come on! Hurry up and give him the bag so that we can get out of this hole!
<se_def>Angelo: Then that'll be the end of this ridiculous distraction!
<se_low>Yangus: I wonder wot 'e meant about givin' Munchie some cheese when we're fightin'?<page>Yangus: He's a cute little fella, an' ev'ryfin', but I don't reckon 'e'd be much use in a brawl.

<se_low>Yangus: But yer never know, do ya?
Let's find ourselves some monsters and give it a go!
<se_high>Jessica: I wonder if he made this cheese himself...?
<se_high>Jessica: Hm, I think we'd probably better give it all to Munchie.
<se_high>Jessica: I draw the line at hermit's cheese! I don't know where he's been! And it didn't seem like he'd left his house in a good while...
<se_def>Angelo: What an eccentric old man! ‘Hello there! Get me my tools and I'll give you some cheese for your ABNORMAL mouse!!!’ Ha ha ha!
<se_def>Angelo: Oh well. If he wants to be weird, it's none of my business. Each to his own and all that.
<se_low>Yangus: Oh no! Looks like that geezer who lives up 'ere ain't in.
<se_high>Jessica: So we've come all this way for nothing. Wonderful.
<se_high>Jessica: I guess we'll have to go all the way back down again. I hate going down steep paths like that. It hurts my feet!
<se_def>Angelo: The scenery up here might be nice, but the inside of that hut's so small you can barely breathe!
<se_def>Angelo: Still, it's an achievement getting anything to perch up here! I've been having trouble keeping myself from sliding down the hill!

<se_low>Yangus: Is it me, or is someone roastin' a chicken in 'ere!?
I'm sweatin' buckets!
<se_low>Yangus: Wot wiv 'im an' all of us squished together, I s'pose it ain't no surprise. But...
<se_low>Yangus: Wot I'm really tryin' to say is that I wanna get out of 'ere...NOW!
<se_high>Jessica: The scenery's gorgeous and the house looks nice from the outside, but it's kind of cramped inside. Don't you think?

<se_high>Jessica: And that's the guy who lives here...
What a let down!
<se_def>Angelo: I thought maybe there'd be a beautiful woman living up here all alone...
<se_def>Angelo: There's no justice in the world!
